abstract: A high school dropout who became New York’s police commissioner received a full pardon for a 2010 conviction on eight felonies.
snippet: A high school dropout who became New York’s police commissioner received a full pardon for a 2010 conviction on eight felonies.
lead_paragraph: Bernard B. Kerik, a onetime New York police commissioner and close ally of former Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani, was one of 11 people to receive executive grants of clemency from President Trump on Tuesday.

abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo, on his first visit to sub-Saharan Africa, promotes partnerships with American companies, but finds China’s presence pervasive.
snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo, on his first visit to sub-Saharan Africa, promotes partnerships with American companies, but finds China’s presence pervasive.
lead_paragraph: NAIROBI, Kenya — When U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo landed in Ethiopia as part of his first foray into sub-Saharan Africa, he arrived in a city shaped by the same adversary that he had come to preach against: China.

abstract: Hoisting the spoils of victories in California’s hard-fought water wars, President Donald Trump is directing more of the state’s precious water to wealthy farmers and other agriculture interests when he visits their Republican Central Valley stronghold Wednesday.
snippet: Hoisting the spoils of victories in California’s hard-fought water wars, President Donald Trump is directing more of the state’s precious water to wealthy farmers and other agriculture interests when he visits their Republican Central Valley stron...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Hoisting the spoils of victories in California’s hard-fought water wars, President Donald Trump is directing more of the state’s precious water to wealthy farmers and other agriculture interests when he visits their Republican Central Valley stronghold Wednesday.
headline_main: Trump Delivers on Pledge for Wealthy California Farmers
headline_print_headline: Trump Delivers on Pledge for Wealthy California Farmers

abstract: Michael Bloomberg, a late entry into the Democratic presidential race, has moved into second place ahead of onetime front-runner Joe Biden, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday that showed Bernie Sanders widening his lead over the field.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg, a late entry into the Democratic presidential race, has moved into second place ahead of onetime front-runner Joe Biden, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday that showed Bernie Sanders widening his lead...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Michael Bloomberg, a late entry into the Democratic presidential race, has moved into second place ahead of onetime front-runner Joe Biden, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday that showed Bernie Sanders widening his lead over the field.
headline_main: Bloomberg Moves Into Second Behind Sanders Among Democrats, Biden Third: Reuters/Ipsos Poll
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Moves Into Second Behind Sanders Among Democrats, Biden Third: Reuters/Ipsos Poll

abstract: President Donald Trump on Tuesday veered into politics during a briefing on preparations for the 2028 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles, criticizing the city's political leadership for failing to curtail its homelessness epidemic.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Tuesday veered into politics during a briefing on preparations for the 2028 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles, criticizing the city's political leadership for failing to curtail its homelessness epidemic.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — President Donald Trump on Tuesday veered into politics during a briefing on preparations for the 2028 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles, criticizing the city's political leadership for failing to curtail its homelessness epidemic.
headline_main: Trump Vows to 'Clean Up' LA at Olympic Meeting Briefing
headline_print_headline: Trump Vows to 'Clean Up' LA at Olympic Meeting Briefing

abstract: A new documentary play at the Public Theater weaves together interviews from people whose lives were forever changed by the 2010 mining disaster in West Virginia.
snippet: A new documentary play at the Public Theater weaves together interviews from people whose lives were forever changed by the 2010 mining disaster in West Virginia.
lead_paragraph: Six years after the explosion that killed 29 coal miners in West Virginia, family members and co-workers of the dead weren’t answering phone calls from the New York playwright.

snippet: Diamond Princess, Chinese media, London Fashion Week: Here’s what you need to know.
lead_paragraph: Japan said that about 500 people would be released from the Diamond Princess, a quarantined cruise ship that has become a hot spot for the coronavirus outbreak, but confusion was widespread about how that would unfold.

abstract: President Trump commuted the sentence of former Gov. Rod R. Blagojevich of Illinois, calling him a “very nice person,” and said he had not considered a pardon for Roger J. Stone Jr, his longest-serving adviser.
